-- Ecuador Plans to Buy $400 Million of Iranian Fuel, Minister Says
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-05-24T16:34:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-24/ecuador-plans-to-buy-400-million-of-iranian-fuel-minister-says.html
Ecuador will buy $400 million of fuel
from  Iran  to cover a shortage in the South American country,
Foreign Minister Ricardo Patino said in a statement e-mailed
late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 